1
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:34,761
The framework proposal

2
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:35,862
has already been approved.

3
00:01:36,029 --> 00:01:37,197
These are the implementation details.

4
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:39,466
Please take a look.

5
00:01:39,799 --> 00:01:41,201
Is there anything else you'd like to add?

6
00:01:42,435 --> 00:01:43,837
There's nothing wrong with the proposal itself.

7
00:01:45,271 --> 00:01:46,172
But afterward, won't you

8
00:01:46,172 --> 00:01:47,173
have to spend a lot of time

9
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,007
at the lower-level hospitals?

10
00:01:48,641 --> 00:01:49,209
No.

11
00:01:49,642 --> 00:01:51,311
I'll still go back and forth like before.

12
00:01:51,444 --> 00:01:52,645
Maybe a little more often.

13
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:54,080
Don't worry.

14
00:01:54,347 --> 00:01:55,014
I won't let

15
00:01:55,048 --> 00:01:55,949
my work here suffer.

16
00:01:57,283 --> 00:01:58,918
Lin Yi usually focuses entirely on surgery.

17
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:00,520
He doesn't pay attention to much else.

18
00:02:01,554 --> 00:02:02,956
His hair has grown long.

19
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:03,723
Why hasn't he thought

20
00:02:03,723 --> 00:02:04,591
about getting a haircut?

21
00:02:08,027 --> 00:02:08,828
What I mean is,

22
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:11,197
we must protect

23
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:13,199
surgical geniuses like Lin Yi.

24
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:14,567
We should minimize

25
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:16,069
the distractions of daily life for him.

26
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:20,173
What does that have to do with this?

27
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:23,476
He just lost a family member.

28
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,311
You're his girlfriend,

29
00:02:25,512 --> 00:02:26,012
his family.

30
00:02:26,746 --> 00:02:28,014
The most important thing right now

31
00:02:28,248 --> 00:02:29,716
is helping him through this period,

32
00:02:30,283 --> 00:02:31,050
supporting him

33
00:02:31,117 --> 00:02:32,652
and being his strong backing.

34
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:34,354
That would also contribute

35
00:02:34,454 --> 00:02:35,088
to the patients

36
00:02:35,188 --> 00:02:35,989
and the department.

37
00:02:38,558 --> 00:02:40,159
I don't understand what you mean.

38
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:42,195
Are you saying

39
00:02:42,228 --> 00:02:42,729
that my work

40
00:02:42,762 --> 00:02:43,530
in the general ICU,

41
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:45,231
serving so many patients,

42
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:46,633
contributes less

43
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:48,868
than making sure Director Lin

44
00:02:48,935 --> 00:02:49,536
gets a haircut?

45
00:02:50,436 --> 00:02:52,038
Don't twist my words.

46
00:02:52,405 --> 00:02:54,274
Think how many patients Lin Yi saves.

47
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:56,242
When they thank him,

48
00:02:56,709 --> 00:02:57,877
don't you share in that credit?

49
00:02:58,912 --> 00:02:59,546
Director Sheng,

50
00:03:00,146 --> 00:03:01,548
surgery is about taking the city.

51
00:03:01,748 --> 00:03:02,081
We,

52
00:03:02,081 --> 00:03:02,682
the general ICU,

53
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:03,316
are the ones defending it.

54
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:05,051
No matter how brilliant your victory,

55
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:05,852
you still need us

56
00:03:05,885 --> 00:03:06,653
in the general ICU

57
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:08,354
for the next twenty-four hours,

58
00:03:08,488 --> 00:03:09,355
forty-eight hours,

59
00:03:09,622 --> 00:03:10,924
or even longer

60
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:12,725
to protect the hard-won result.

61
00:03:13,626 --> 00:03:14,561
Director Lin and I

62
00:03:14,794 --> 00:03:16,362
have never been in a subordinate relationship.

63
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:18,631
We're equal partners.

64
00:03:19,332 --> 00:03:20,600
Don't be so sensitive.

65
00:03:21,134 --> 00:03:21,801
I'm saying

66
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:24,070
this matter isn't that urgent.

67
00:03:25,238 --> 00:03:25,972
Maybe someone else

68
00:03:26,005 --> 00:03:26,773
could take over for you

69
00:03:26,906 --> 00:03:27,840
for the time being.

70
00:03:28,608 --> 00:03:30,210
It's more urgent than Director Lin's haircut.

71
00:03:31,544 --> 00:03:32,111
I designed and coordinated

72
00:03:32,111 --> 00:03:33,279
this entire plan.

73
00:03:33,279 --> 00:03:34,514
It would be hard for anyone else to take over quickly.

74
00:03:34,814 --> 00:03:36,182
I've poured my heart into it for a long time.

75
00:03:36,983 --> 00:03:38,051
And I haven't done anything wrong.

76
00:03:38,117 --> 00:03:39,085
Why should I be replaced?

77
00:03:39,152 --> 00:03:39,852
Why are you getting so worked up?

78
00:03:45,024 --> 00:03:46,125
I'm only asking your opinion

79
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:46,826
and discussing it with you.

80
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:48,394
My opinion is

81
00:03:48,761 --> 00:03:49,629
that I will not give up

82
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:50,330
this project.

83
00:03:50,830 --> 00:03:52,432
It's one of my most important duties.

84
00:03:58,605 --> 00:03:59,105
All right.

85
00:04:00,106 --> 00:04:01,174
Then make sure

86
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:03,309
you balance work and rest.

87
00:04:03,509 --> 00:04:04,344
You need to distinguish

88
00:04:05,211 --> 00:04:06,012
what matters most.

89
00:04:09,048 --> 00:04:09,482
I will.

90
00:04:20,126 --> 00:04:20,827
Dr. Fang is back.

91
00:04:24,797 --> 00:04:26,065
What did Director Sheng say?

92
00:04:27,634 --> 00:04:28,534
Xiao Du, let me ask you something.

93
00:04:29,302 --> 00:04:30,503
Do you think Dr. Lin's

94
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:31,704
hair is too long?

95
00:04:32,572 --> 00:04:33,473
It's okay.

96
00:04:37,076 --> 00:04:38,144
Maybe a little.

97
00:04:38,244 --> 00:04:38,945
Now that you mention it...

98
00:04:40,246 --> 00:04:42,015
Does it affect his surgery?

99
00:04:42,281 --> 00:04:43,716
Does it affect his clinic?

100
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:45,351
Of course not in clinic.

101
00:04:45,551 --> 00:04:46,719
And in surgery,

102
00:04:47,553 --> 00:04:48,655
we wear caps anyway.

103
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:49,255
Exactly.

104
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:50,723
What era are we living in?

105
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:51,824
All this talk about women

106
00:04:51,891 --> 00:04:53,326
standing behind geniuses.

107
00:04:53,559 --> 00:04:54,794
Don't I get to have my own ambitions?

108
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:55,762
Don't I have my own work

109
00:04:55,762 --> 00:04:56,195
to do?

110
00:04:56,362 --> 00:04:57,664
Of course you can have your own goals.

111
00:04:58,064 --> 00:04:58,531
Dr. Fang,

112
00:04:58,831 --> 00:05:00,800
my mom goes to senior college every day now,

113
00:05:00,933 --> 00:05:02,001
joins a modeling team and square dancing.

114
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:03,369
She's busier than when she worked.

115
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:04,304
She has tons of goals.

116
00:05:04,504 --> 00:05:05,238
And Dr. Fang,

117
00:05:05,705 --> 00:05:06,239
think about it.

118
00:05:06,706 --> 00:05:07,840
What you're doing

119
00:05:07,907 --> 00:05:08,875
to build general ICUs at lower-level hospitals

120
00:05:08,875 --> 00:05:09,309
is something

121
00:05:09,409 --> 00:05:10,443
we've all seen.

122
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:11,878
I think you're amazing.

123
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,112
To us, you're

124
00:05:13,446 --> 00:05:14,547
Mu Guiying, Hua Mulan,

125
00:05:14,847 --> 00:05:15,515
Marie Curie,

126
00:05:15,615 --> 00:05:16,249
and Fang Xiaoran.

127
00:05:19,052 --> 00:05:19,719
All right, all right.

128
00:05:19,852 --> 00:05:20,520
That's enough.

129
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:21,688
I'm serious.

130
00:05:22,255 --> 00:05:23,556
You're the most energetic

131
00:05:23,623 --> 00:05:24,223
superwoman I've ever met.

132
00:05:25,525 --> 00:05:26,759
All right. Back to work.

133
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,695
Help me

134
00:05:28,695 --> 00:05:29,595
check the data and details

135
00:05:29,595 --> 00:05:30,530
one last time.

136
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:32,065
If there are no problems, we'll leave it.

137
00:05:32,365 --> 00:05:33,266
Then send it directly to President Xu.

138
00:05:33,566 --> 00:05:33,866
Okay.

139
00:05:34,767 --> 00:05:35,635
Not angry anymore, Dr. Fang?

140
00:05:46,412 --> 00:05:47,947
Professor Peng was really handsome when he was young.

141
00:05:48,281 --> 00:05:48,948
Very handsome.

142
00:05:49,215 --> 00:05:49,849
Back then,

143
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:52,585
he taught our European literature class.

144
00:05:52,985 --> 00:05:53,986
I secretly took

145
00:05:54,654 --> 00:05:55,388
this photo

146
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:56,756
when I attended

147
00:05:57,156 --> 00:05:58,124
one of his public lectures.

148
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:00,326
He could always make serious

149
00:06:00,393 --> 00:06:01,427
and profound material

150
00:06:02,395 --> 00:06:03,830
vivid and engaging,

151
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:05,598
full of life.

152
00:06:09,802 --> 00:06:11,671
Whenever he taught,

153
00:06:12,171 --> 00:06:12,805
the classroom

154
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,841
and even the aisles were packed.

155
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:20,012
But now,

156
00:06:20,813 --> 00:06:21,948
time has worn us down.

157
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:25,184
We've both grown old.

158
00:06:27,086 --> 00:06:28,321
Don't be too sad.

159
00:06:28,988 --> 00:06:30,590
None of us can fight time.

160
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:32,592
But Professor Peng

161
00:06:32,592 --> 00:06:33,493
has had you by his side all these years.

162
00:06:33,526 --> 00:06:34,394
He's very fortunate.

163
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:36,062
That's right, Ms. Jiang.

164
00:06:36,429 --> 00:06:37,764
I believe Professor Peng

165
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:39,465
will recover quickly for your sake.

166
00:06:40,199 --> 00:06:40,666
He will.

167
00:06:42,635 --> 00:06:43,269
Thank you.

168
00:06:46,372 --> 00:06:47,707
Stay with him for now.

169
00:06:48,007 --> 00:06:49,008
Call us anytime if you need anything.

170
00:06:49,509 --> 00:06:49,876
Okay.

171
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:50,843
Let's read.

172
00:06:52,945 --> 00:06:53,646
Where did we

173
00:06:54,614 --> 00:06:55,681
leave off last time?

174
00:06:55,948 --> 00:06:56,649
Do you remember?

175
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:02,288
While alive,

176
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:05,391
one should never pretend or deceive.

177
00:07:06,993 --> 00:07:07,727
And so,

178
00:07:08,795 --> 00:07:09,562
I slept soundly,

179
00:07:10,797 --> 00:07:11,664
quietly recalling

180
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:14,066
that newspaper article.

181
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:17,003
Day followed night,

182
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:18,905
one day after another,

183
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:22,475
and time passed.

184
00:07:27,547 --> 00:07:28,114
You're exhausted.

185
00:07:28,648 --> 00:07:30,016
Another sleepless night shift?

186
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:35,254
Every time I lay down, my phone rang.

187
00:07:35,755 --> 00:07:37,690
The ward called one after another,

188
00:07:37,990 --> 00:07:39,325
like a soul-snatching alarm.

189
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:41,327
I spent the whole night doing sit-ups.

190
00:07:41,394 --> 00:07:42,295
It never stopped.

191
00:07:43,029 --> 00:07:44,063
Then why aren't you going home?

192
00:07:45,431 --> 00:07:46,766
I still have charts to finish.

193
00:07:47,533 --> 00:07:49,268
And discharge summaries

194
00:07:49,335 --> 00:07:50,837
for Director Lin's surgical patients.

195
00:07:51,437 --> 00:07:51,804
Here.

196
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:53,706
True.

197
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,408
You're running between two departments,

198
00:07:55,408 --> 00:07:56,008
working nonstop,

199
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:57,210
and taking consecutive overnight shifts.

200
00:07:58,044 --> 00:07:58,911
Are you trying to evolve

201
00:07:59,011 --> 00:07:59,846
beyond the need for sleep?

202
00:08:00,346 --> 00:08:01,247
Careful, you'll drop dead.

203
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:02,915
I won't die.

204
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:05,685
It's just that relations

205
00:08:05,718 --> 00:08:06,786
between the two departments are awkward now.

206
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,121
And I'm still apprenticing under

207
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,122
both Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery.

208
00:08:11,090 --> 00:08:12,358
That makes it even more awkward.

209
00:08:13,593 --> 00:08:14,560
What's awkward about it?

210
00:08:14,794 --> 00:08:15,795
You wouldn't understand.

211
00:08:20,066 --> 00:08:20,800
I heard

212
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:21,734
Jiang Huichu

213
00:08:21,734 --> 00:08:22,535
is still difficult in the general ICU.

214
00:08:22,535 --> 00:08:23,302
is still difficult in the general ICU.

215
00:08:24,804 --> 00:08:25,805
That's not entirely fair.

216
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:28,007
She just cares deeply about Professor Peng,

217
00:08:28,507 --> 00:08:29,509
so she gets anxious easily.

218
00:08:30,209 --> 00:08:31,911
His beard isn't cleanly shaved.

219
00:08:32,111 --> 00:08:32,545
Look.

220
00:08:32,912 --> 00:08:33,880
There are still two hairs here.

221
00:08:35,081 --> 00:08:35,882
We can't

222
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:36,749
cut corners

223
00:08:36,949 --> 00:08:37,984
just because he can't speak.

224
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:38,651
Fine.

225
00:08:38,718 --> 00:08:39,685
We'll shave him again later.

226
00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:44,624
His nails are cut too short.

227
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,126
That can cause paronychia.

228
00:08:49,161 --> 00:08:49,962
Why is his hand

229
00:08:49,996 --> 00:08:51,030
tied so tightly?

230
00:08:51,063 --> 00:08:52,798
That'll restrict circulation.

231
00:08:53,766 --> 00:08:54,467
Although he's

232
00:08:54,533 --> 00:08:55,601
sedated right now,

233
00:08:56,002 --> 00:08:56,636
he can still become agitated

234
00:08:56,636 --> 00:08:57,803
and uncomfortable sometimes,

235
00:08:57,803 --> 00:08:58,905
and try to pull out the endotracheal tube.

236
00:08:59,171 --> 00:09:00,473
We have to secure him tightly.

237
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,574
But don't worry.

238
00:09:01,908 --> 00:09:02,241
Look.

239
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:03,543
These are protective restraints.

240
00:09:03,609 --> 00:09:04,510
They won't hurt him.

241
00:09:05,912 --> 00:09:07,313
Actually, I think Ms. Jiang

242
00:09:07,914 --> 00:09:08,748
hasn't had it easy.

243
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:10,449
She's also tough.

244
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:12,385
Her family member is hospitalized,

245
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:13,486
yet she still dared to sue the hospital

246
00:09:14,086 --> 00:09:15,788
and drag Director Zhou into it.

247
00:09:17,156 --> 00:09:17,990
I'm telling you,

248
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:19,892
watch what you say.

249
00:09:20,092 --> 00:09:21,360
Don't give anyone leverage against you.

250
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:27,066
Hello?

251
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:28,267
Which bed?

252
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,469
Okay, I'm coming.

253
00:09:31,103 --> 00:09:32,605
I have to go. Help me put this away.

254
00:09:47,853 --> 00:09:48,688
Dr. Du.

255
00:09:50,289 --> 00:09:50,790
Ms. Jiang.

256
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:52,525
Could I take two minutes of your time?

257
00:09:53,292 --> 00:09:54,126
What is it?

258
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:56,596
I have an unreasonable request.

259
00:09:58,731 --> 00:09:59,231
Go ahead.

260
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:00,633
I was wondering

261
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:02,802
whether you could help me

262
00:10:03,803 --> 00:10:04,370
What kind of help?

263
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:06,706
Could you

264
00:10:07,006 --> 00:10:08,007
call Professor Peng's son

265
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:08,774
for me?

266
00:10:08,975 --> 00:10:09,642
I...

267
00:10:09,909 --> 00:10:10,543
I can call.

268
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,445
What I mean is, if possible,

269
00:10:12,845 --> 00:10:14,547
I'd like you to explain

270
00:10:14,647 --> 00:10:16,515
his father's condition in detail.

271
00:10:19,385 --> 00:10:21,587
That day, I borrowed the nurses' station phone

272
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:22,688
to call his son.

273
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:24,223
He shouted very loudly.

274
00:10:24,690 --> 00:10:26,092
I'm sure Dr. Du

275
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:26,993
heard it too.

276
00:10:27,727 --> 00:10:28,527
No, no, no.

277
00:10:31,864 --> 00:10:33,633
I only heard a little.

278
00:10:37,436 --> 00:10:38,471
Professor Peng's son

279
00:10:39,238 --> 00:10:39,905
has always misunderstood us.

280
00:10:40,673 --> 00:10:41,707
He thinks

281
00:10:42,575 --> 00:10:43,542
I broke up

282
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:44,677
his parents' marriage.

283
00:10:44,944 --> 00:10:45,511
So

284
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,480
he hasn't come home

285
00:10:47,546 --> 00:10:48,681
for many years.

286
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:50,282
But I truly didn't.

287
00:10:50,649 --> 00:10:51,350
We only got together

288
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:53,185
a year after their divorce.

289
00:10:53,753 --> 00:10:55,287
Professor Peng rarely mentions it,

290
00:10:55,554 --> 00:10:56,322
but I know

291
00:10:56,555 --> 00:10:57,790
he misses his son deeply.

292
00:10:57,957 --> 00:10:59,291
He's his only son.

293
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:03,829
Especially now,

294
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:07,133
he has made a will for him.

295
00:11:07,466 --> 00:11:08,034
I hope

296
00:11:10,803 --> 00:11:12,204
Professor Peng can have his wish fulfilled.

297
00:11:14,673 --> 00:11:15,574
Then give me his number.

298
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:17,343
Thank you.

299
00:11:23,749 --> 00:11:24,650
The lawyer is here.

300
00:11:31,424 --> 00:11:32,692
The will has been revised

301
00:11:32,825 --> 00:11:33,793
according to your wishes.

302
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:34,927
Please review it carefully.

303
00:11:38,164 --> 00:11:39,231
Whatever she decides is fine.

304
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:41,033
Please look it over carefully.

305
00:11:42,334 --> 00:11:43,669
There's nothing for me to review.

306
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:44,570
I already said

307
00:11:45,237 --> 00:11:46,272
I don't want a cent

308
00:11:46,305 --> 00:11:47,173
of his personal property.

309
00:11:47,473 --> 00:11:48,174
It all goes to his son.

310
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:50,042
Here. Keep it safe.

311
00:12:00,453 --> 00:12:01,320
Wasn't the appointment for ten?

312
00:12:01,487 --> 00:12:02,088
Why isn't he here yet?

313
00:12:03,155 --> 00:12:04,790
That's what Dr. Du said.

314
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:07,927
He...

315
00:12:08,327 --> 00:12:09,495
Are you sure he'll come?

316
00:12:10,196 --> 00:12:11,330
At least he didn't refuse.

317
00:12:12,364 --> 00:12:13,399
Didn't you say

318
00:12:13,766 --> 00:12:15,634
their family isn't well-off?

319
00:12:16,168 --> 00:12:16,502
Then...

320
00:12:16,769 --> 00:12:18,704
At least for the money,

321
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:21,607
I've already told him the amount.

322
00:12:22,007 --> 00:12:22,775
We even

323
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:24,410
sent him a text message

324
00:12:26,045 --> 00:12:27,413
saying ten o'clock.

325
00:12:27,746 --> 00:12:28,614
Don't worry.

326
00:12:28,881 --> 00:12:29,715
Let's wait a little longer.

327
00:12:31,684 --> 00:12:32,118
Dr. Fang.

328
00:12:34,987 --> 00:12:35,354
Go ahead.

329
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:43,195
Ms. Jiang.

330
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:46,632
He replied.

331
00:12:47,032 --> 00:12:47,533
What did he say?

332
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:51,303
Quickly. Give it to me.

333
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:53,205
Quickly.

334
00:12:54,406 --> 00:12:55,374
Give it to me.

335
00:12:58,344 --> 00:12:59,078
Dr. Du,

336
00:12:59,712 --> 00:13:00,846
tell that woman

337
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:02,248
I don't want the money

338
00:13:02,748 --> 00:13:03,382
and I won't see him.

339
00:13:04,517 --> 00:13:05,751
Let that woman see him off.

340
00:13:07,686 --> 00:13:08,687
Don't get worked up.

341
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:10,189
You can't do this.

342
00:13:10,189 --> 00:13:11,223
Your body can't take it.

343
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,025
I'll talk to him again.

344
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:14,560
Don't worry. It'll be okay.

345
00:13:15,227 --> 00:13:15,761
Listen to me.

346
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:16,996
You can't cry.

347
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:19,131
You can't get this agitated.

348
00:13:19,365 --> 00:13:19,932
Listen to me.

349
00:13:28,274 --> 00:13:28,807
Dr. Xiaoran.

350
00:13:30,943 --> 00:13:31,944
Did you draw an arterial blood gas?

351
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:32,545
Yes.

352
00:13:43,856 --> 00:13:44,990
This is the situation

353
00:13:45,024 --> 00:13:45,925
we most hoped to avoid.

354
00:13:46,892 --> 00:13:48,027
The emotional shock

355
00:13:48,327 --> 00:13:49,929
worsened his lung infection.

356
00:13:50,763 --> 00:13:51,764
We gave him

357
00:13:51,864 --> 00:13:52,865
high-flow oxygen

358
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:54,366
and noninvasive ventilation,

359
00:13:55,034 --> 00:13:56,735
but his hypoxia never improved.

360
00:13:57,369 --> 00:13:58,671
So we had to intubate him again.

361
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:00,506
Then...

362
00:14:03,442 --> 00:14:05,644
he'll be sedated again?

363
00:14:07,046 --> 00:14:07,446
Yes.

364
00:14:09,281 --> 00:14:10,049
But we're still

365
00:14:10,115 --> 00:14:11,250
actively working on solutions.

366
00:14:12,117 --> 00:14:12,985
We'll tell you immediately

367
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:14,386
if there is any progress.

368
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:17,990
Okay.

369
00:14:36,742 --> 00:14:37,643
There was a traffic accident.

370
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:44,216
How is he?

371
00:14:44,516 --> 00:14:45,384
That was a hard hit.

372
00:14:47,253 --> 00:14:48,254
Get him to the hospital.

373
00:14:48,454 --> 00:14:49,288
Call 120.

374
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:54,426
Dr. Wang.

375
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:55,728
What's the situation?

376
00:14:56,028 --> 00:14:56,595
Sisi is here.

377
00:14:57,596 --> 00:14:58,130
Take a look.

378
00:14:58,631 --> 00:14:59,598
This young man

379
00:14:59,765 --> 00:15:01,033
was just hit by an electric scooter.

380
00:15:01,767 --> 00:15:02,801
The external injuries aren't serious,

381
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:03,369
but his quantitative

382
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:04,436
heart-failure biomarker is extremely high.

383
00:15:04,903 --> 00:15:05,271
So

384
00:15:05,271 --> 00:15:06,038
I did an echocardiogram

385
00:15:06,038 --> 00:15:06,705
and an ECG.

386
00:15:06,972 --> 00:15:07,506
Take another look.

387
00:15:19,451 --> 00:15:20,719
His cardiac function is terrible.

388
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:25,157
Have you notified his family?

389
00:15:25,524 --> 00:15:26,091
Yes.

390
00:15:26,325 --> 00:15:26,959
They're on the way.

391
00:15:27,526 --> 00:15:28,193
I can handle it myself.

392
00:15:29,495 --> 00:15:30,162
You don't need to call them.

393
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:32,164
Doctor. Doctor.

394
00:15:32,665 --> 00:15:33,198
Can I ask

395
00:15:33,198 --> 00:15:34,266
what's wrong with him?

396
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,769
There's something wrong with his heart.

397
00:15:37,069 --> 00:15:37,670
And

398
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:38,904
it's quite serious.

399
00:15:39,571 --> 00:15:40,039
His heart?

400
00:15:40,839 --> 00:15:42,775
I wasn't riding that fast.

401
00:15:42,808 --> 00:15:44,076
How could I have hit his heart?

402
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:44,310
This...

403
00:15:44,910 --> 00:15:45,844
I wasn't watching the road.

404
00:15:45,911 --> 00:15:46,312
It's not your fault.

405
00:15:50,683 --> 00:15:51,383
Do you usually have

406
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:52,584
any cardiac symptoms?

407
00:15:52,918 --> 00:15:54,186
For example, shortness of breath,

408
00:15:54,353 --> 00:15:55,154
breathlessness, or trouble lying flat?

409
00:15:56,989 --> 00:15:57,356
This didn't

410
00:15:57,356 --> 00:15:58,223
start a day or two ago.

411
00:16:00,693 --> 00:16:01,126
Sisi.

412
00:16:01,994 --> 00:16:02,895
I think

413
00:16:02,928 --> 00:16:03,829
we should admit him to your unit.

414
00:16:05,831 --> 00:16:06,131
He needs

415
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:06,865
the general ICU.

416
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:16,742
He's admitted.

417
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:19,111
Dr. Fang.

418
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:26,585
It looks congenital.

419
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:27,886
Left ventricular noncompaction,

420
00:16:27,953 --> 00:16:28,954
left ventricular hypoplasia,

421
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:30,990
and possibly

422
00:16:31,023 --> 00:16:32,124
malignant arrhythmias.

423
00:16:34,526 --> 00:16:35,761
He's only seventeen.

424
00:16:40,599 --> 00:16:42,634
Is this your bag?

425
00:16:45,237 --> 00:16:46,872
Aren't all those badges heavy?

426
00:16:48,073 --> 00:16:48,607
Beibei.

427
00:16:49,241 --> 00:16:50,642
This is trendy now.

428
00:16:57,249 --> 00:16:58,183
A five-jin bag

429
00:16:58,450 --> 00:16:59,351
with ten jin of badges.

430
00:17:00,319 --> 00:17:01,453
I need to

431
00:17:01,453 --> 00:17:01,987
educate you on this.

432
00:17:02,388 --> 00:17:03,389
It's very popular now.

433
00:17:03,789 --> 00:17:04,690
I don't understand

434
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:05,557
what you young people

435
00:17:05,724 --> 00:17:06,725
are into these days.

436
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:07,926
Young people?

437
00:17:08,594 --> 00:17:09,161
Sister Xiaoran,

438
00:17:09,161 --> 00:17:10,028
you're young too.

439
00:17:10,396 --> 00:17:11,397
If the two of us sit together,

440
00:17:13,132 --> 00:17:13,532
Xiaoyu,

441
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,000
my little sister.

442
00:17:15,734 --> 00:17:16,535
Ridiculous.

443
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:22,307
It looks good.

444
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:23,809
When your parents arrive,

445
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:25,277
I'll have them keep it for you.

446
00:17:26,412 --> 00:17:28,047
Can't I just leave it here?

447
00:17:28,447 --> 00:17:28,747
No.

448
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:29,915
The ICU has rules.

449
00:17:30,149 --> 00:17:31,116
It's better for your parents to keep it.

450
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:31,683
It's better for your parents to keep it.

451
00:17:34,353 --> 00:17:34,887
I'll go now.

452
00:17:56,308 --> 00:17:57,309
Are you blind?

453
00:17:57,509 --> 00:17:58,544
You couldn't see a living person?

454
00:17:58,644 --> 00:17:59,311
I saw him.

455
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:00,112
No, I didn't.

456
00:18:00,312 --> 00:18:01,613
I really wasn't riding fast.

457
00:18:01,647 --> 00:18:02,114
I don't know how

458
00:18:02,147 --> 00:18:03,282
I somehow hit his heart.

459
00:18:03,315 --> 00:18:04,850
You delivery riders

460
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:06,251
race around recklessly all day.

461
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:08,120
My son is only seventeen.

462
00:18:08,153 --> 00:18:08,787
Listen carefully.

463
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:10,722
If anything happens to my child,

464
00:18:10,722 --> 00:18:11,557
Watch your tone.

465
00:18:11,990 --> 00:18:12,624
Give me your ID.

466
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,159
Don't think you can run. Give it to me.

467
00:18:14,593 --> 00:18:15,561
One thing at a time.

468
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:16,795
Listen to me first.

469
00:18:16,995 --> 00:18:17,563
Don't get agitated.

470
00:18:17,863 --> 00:18:18,997
We're already running tests

471
00:18:19,031 --> 00:18:19,798
on your son.

472
00:18:20,399 --> 00:18:21,166
His heart disease

473
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:21,967
is most likely congenital.

474
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:22,768
It wasn't caused by the collision.

475
00:18:22,968 --> 00:18:24,470
Doctor, you can't say that.

476
00:18:24,670 --> 00:18:25,504
My son has always

477
00:18:25,504 --> 00:18:26,572
been perfectly healthy.

478
00:18:26,572 --> 00:18:27,873
He never had any illness.

479
00:18:28,307 --> 00:18:29,975
That man injured him.

480
00:18:30,275 --> 00:18:32,611
Doctor, you need to be reasonable.

481
00:18:32,811 --> 00:18:34,279
I'm telling you the facts.

482
00:18:34,546 --> 00:18:35,814
Without this accident,

483
00:18:35,848 --> 00:18:37,082
you might not have discovered it yet.

484
00:18:37,916 --> 00:18:39,151
It could have flared up someday anyway.

485
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:40,886
How can you talk like that?

486
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:41,920
What did he give you?

487
00:18:42,254 --> 00:18:43,722
Exactly. What's your relationship?

488
00:18:43,755 --> 00:18:44,957
That's not what I meant.

489
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:45,958
But one issue is one issue.

490
00:18:46,024 --> 00:18:46,892
What about his external injuries?

491
00:18:47,392 --> 00:18:48,727
The collision caused those.

492
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:49,995
He's lying in there right now.

493
00:18:50,095 --> 00:18:50,729
Why are you arguing?

494
00:18:53,031 --> 00:18:53,665
Director.

495
00:18:54,199 --> 00:18:54,800
Leader.

496
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:57,469
Your young doctor is talking nonsense.

497
00:18:57,769 --> 00:18:58,437
A doctor is a doctor.

498
00:18:58,804 --> 00:18:59,605
There are no big or small doctors.

499
00:19:00,405 --> 00:19:00,873
What's going on?

500
00:19:01,039 --> 00:19:01,507
She says my child

501
00:19:01,507 --> 00:19:02,374
already had heart disease.

502
00:19:02,508 --> 00:19:03,308
How could that be?

503
00:19:04,343 --> 00:19:04,910
Which patient?

504
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:06,111
I admitted him from the ER.

505
00:19:06,245 --> 00:19:07,246
He's been transferred to Director Zhou.

506
00:19:07,713 --> 00:19:08,247
Most likely

507
00:19:08,280 --> 00:19:09,348
left ventricular noncompaction.

508
00:19:09,748 --> 00:19:11,683
Our child was always healthy.

509
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:13,318
What exactly do you want?

510
00:19:14,686 --> 00:19:16,822
He injured him and must take responsibility.

511
00:19:17,256 --> 00:19:17,990
That's between you.

512
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,091
It has nothing to do with the doctors.

513
00:19:19,491 --> 00:19:20,225
The attending physician

514
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:20,993
will come out

515
00:19:21,026 --> 00:19:21,560
and explain the child's condition.

516
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:22,694
Wait here quietly.

517
00:19:22,928 --> 00:19:23,595
How can it have nothing to do with you?

518
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:24,463
She says my child

519
00:19:24,463 --> 00:19:25,230
was born with heart disease.

520
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:25,964
He caused it.

521
00:19:25,964 --> 00:19:26,832
Du Yan's family.

522
00:19:26,865 --> 00:19:27,666
I was only stating the facts.

523
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:28,400
Du Yan's family.

524
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,401
Here. I'm here.

525
00:19:30,035 --> 00:19:31,236
Are you Du Yan's parents?

526
00:19:31,370 --> 00:19:31,803
Yes, yes.

527
00:19:32,905 --> 00:19:33,839
This is his bag, right?

528
00:19:33,906 --> 00:19:34,473
Yes. That's it.

529
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:35,507
Keep it safe.

530
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:36,775
Doctor,

531
00:19:37,276 --> 00:19:39,044
how is my son?

532
00:19:39,444 --> 00:19:40,746
When visiting hours begin,

533
00:19:40,946 --> 00:19:41,747
go in and ask the doctor.

534
00:19:42,214 --> 00:19:43,348
You have to save him.

535
00:19:43,448 --> 00:19:44,082
Why are you just standing there?

536
00:19:50,355 --> 00:19:51,957
You interfere in other people's business too?

537
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:54,493
I learned from you.

538
00:19:54,826 --> 00:19:56,361
You need a sense of justice and duty

539
00:19:56,428 --> 00:19:57,129
to deserve

540
00:19:57,162 --> 00:19:58,263
the white coat you're wearing.

541
00:19:59,431 --> 00:20:00,666
You're you. I'm me.

542
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:02,334
You'll be doomed if you copy me.

543
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:06,204
Director Lin,

544
00:20:07,439 --> 00:20:09,675
haven't you and Director Zhou made up yet?

545
00:20:10,742 --> 00:20:12,277
I just think it's such a pity.

546
00:20:12,844 --> 00:20:13,679
When the two of you work together,

547
00:20:13,679 --> 00:20:14,813
you can help even more patients.

548
00:20:16,114 --> 00:20:16,848
You have too much free time.

549
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:18,684
Why meddle in so much?

550
00:20:21,653 --> 00:20:22,354
Dr. Ye.

551
00:20:24,756 --> 00:20:25,190
Xiao Du.

552
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:26,692
We'll do a physical examination first.

553
00:20:26,792 --> 00:20:27,526
Tell me immediately

554
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:28,227
if anything feels uncomfortable

555
00:20:28,293 --> 00:20:29,027
during the exam.

556
00:20:29,761 --> 00:20:30,696
Xiao Du, don't be nervous.

557
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:31,430
My surname is Du too.

558
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,065
Come on. Let me first check

559
00:20:33,131 --> 00:20:34,266
your wounds.

560
00:20:35,601 --> 00:20:36,535
There are some abrasions.

561
00:20:42,608 --> 00:20:43,208
Didn't I already

562
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:44,643
have a lot of tests?

563
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:46,345
Machine-based tests

564
00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:47,212
are only supplementary.

565
00:20:47,546 --> 00:20:48,046
A careful

566
00:20:48,046 --> 00:20:48,947
physical examination by a doctor

567
00:20:49,014 --> 00:20:50,415
helps us understand your condition

568
00:20:50,482 --> 00:20:51,750
more comprehensively and precisely.

569
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:02,995
Why do you have so many

570
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:03,929
old injuries here?

571
00:21:06,765 --> 00:21:07,232
I fell.

572
00:21:10,402 --> 00:21:10,869
How did you fall?

573
00:21:11,703 --> 00:21:12,771
Down a mountain.

574
00:21:22,848 --> 00:21:23,315
Sisi.

575
00:21:26,184 --> 00:21:26,985
What about these?

576
00:21:30,255 --> 00:21:30,989
I fell too.

577
00:21:35,594 --> 00:21:36,395
Visiting hours have begun.

578
00:21:36,695 --> 00:21:38,063
Family members, please enter in order.

579
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,199
That's all for today.

580
00:21:43,035 --> 00:21:43,669
Get some rest.

581
00:21:43,769 --> 00:21:44,236
Doctor.

582
00:21:44,436 --> 00:21:45,570
Where is Du Yan?

583
00:21:45,604 --> 00:21:46,638
Bed 13.

584
00:21:50,842 --> 00:21:51,343
Son.

585
00:21:53,445 --> 00:21:54,913
Let Mom see where it hurts.

586
00:21:58,917 --> 00:22:00,085
Is your heart uncomfortable?

587
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:00,585
Is it?

588
00:22:01,053 --> 00:22:01,520
No.

589
00:22:02,354 --> 00:22:03,322
It's fine. I brought you something good.

590
00:22:04,022 --> 00:22:04,456
Doctor.

